93890.name: Exports to the North (OWID calculations based on CEPII (2016))
93890.description: Merchandise exports to countries in the North.
93890.datasetName: Exports to different country groupings - OWID calculations based on CEPII (2016)

source.name: CEPII North-South groupings (2016)
source.dataPublishedBy: Michel Fouquin & Jules Hugot , 2016. "Two Centuries of Bilateral Trade and Gravity Data: 1827-2014," CEPII Working Paper 2016- 14 , May 2016 , CEPII
source.dataPublisherSource: IMF Direction of Trade Statistics data set, manuscripts
source.additionalInfo:
North countries include: Australia, Canada, Japan, New Zealand, the United States, Austria, Belgium, Denmark, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Italy, the Netherlands, Norway, Portugal, Russia, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, the United Kingdom. This classification has been derived from the UN Human Development Report (2013), Figure 2.1, available here: http://hdr.undp.org/sites/default/files/reports/14/hdr2013_en_complete.pdf.

The remaining countries in the data set comprise the South.

The data series for Germany includes East and West Germany for the period 1950-1990.
